// Reference for rewrite_broadcast_min_1.daphne: the same value computed in the
// already-regrouped form (M1 + M2) + (s1 + s2). The scalars are summed once and
// the matrices added directly, so there is no (M1 + s1) + (M2 + s2) shape for the
// broadcast-minimization rewrite to match. The modular result must match the
// rewritten form byte for byte, including the scalar-sum overflow.

M1 = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6];
M1 = reshape(M1, 2, 3);
M2 = [10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60];
M2 = reshape(M2, 2, 3);

s1 = 4611686018427387904;
s2 = 4611686018427387905;

print((M1 + M2) + (s1 + s2));
